  "prompt": "Where does the word \"suicide\" come from?",
  "response": "The word \"suicide\" comes from the Latin \"suicidium,\" which is a combination of two parts: \"sui,\" meaning \"of oneself,\" and \"caedere,\" meaning \"to kill.\" Thus, the term essentially means \"to kill oneself.\" The use of the word in English can be traced back to the late 17th century. The concept of suicide has been present in various cultures and societies throughout history, and discussions around it have evolved significantly over time, particularly in terms of mental health awareness and social attitudes.",
